Reunited P-Square brothers Peter and Paul Okoye have hinted at a new song/album release after five years of being apart. Although the Okoye brothers have been doing music separately, this is the first time they will be teasing a new song or album release on social media following their reconciliation after a 5-year separation. In their respective social media pages, Mr P and Rudeboy shared a photo that displayed both of them. While Mr P captioned the post: ““You’re ready? ……….incoming!” Rudeboy’s caption reads: “Incoming.”   S3x- for-role claims in Nollywood untrue – Kanayo O Kanayo     Nigerian Idol 7: Winner to get N100m as Binance, Bigi join…     Jaruma remanded after Regina Daniel’s husband petition   - Advertisement - The duo announced their reunion in November 2021 and left fan absolutely ecstatic with their first concert in years on the 25th of December 2021 at the Live X Spot Festival in Lagos. The concert was graced by top celebrities and fans who had missed the multi-talented twin brothers doing what they know best together. The multiple award-winning duos had also hinted at a world tour, an announcement that left fans electrified. Rudeboy made the announcement via his Twitter page on Friday, January 14, 2022. Sharing a video of their stellar performance at their 2021 Christmas concert, the singer tweeted, “Psquare world tour loading.”